content: So I noticed for a majority of the dirt tunes, the recommended setting is toe out, up to two clicks sometimes. You NEVER want toe out in the rear of pretty much any car in any circumstances. This makes the car very unstable at speeds and oversteer s uncontrollably.
replyContent: Actually dirt tunes use front toe in which promotes understeer on corner entry and rear toe out which promotes understeer on corner exit, so Dirt tunes have more understeer bias as compared to road tunes. What cars are you using for Dirt?
